---
import ColorLayout from '../../color-app/ColorLayout.astro';
---

<ColorLayout title="ben's colors // about" currPage="about">
  <div class="about-page">
    <h1 class="about-title">about</h1>
    <div class="about-rule"></div>

    <div class="about-body">
      <p>
        This is a tiny set of tools I use to browse color palettes and color books.
      </p>
      <p>
        This repository uses the Adobe Color Book format (ACB). You can find an open-source parser at
        <a class="colors-link" href="https://github.com/jacobbubu/acb" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">This repository</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        The raw color books for this site live
        <a class="colors-link" href="https://github.com/64bitpandas/bencuan.me/tree/main/src/color-books" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">here</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        The default accent is
        <a class="colors-link" href="https://catppuccin.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Catppuccin blue</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        Click here:
        <a class="colors-link" href="https://bencuan.me" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Click here</a>
      </p>
      <p>
        State of Vibe Coding evaluation:
        <a class="colors-link" href="https://bencuan.me/blog/vibe25" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">State of Vibe Coding evaluation</a>
      </p>
      <p>
        Built by GitHub Copilot.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</ColorLayout>
